set10-004.author: Gabriel Quinn / Jules Dubost
set10-004.flavorText: Manny was looking to get ahead, but he'd never considered that something in the Inkwell Caverns was looking for him.

set10-005.author: Narges Jafari

set10-006.author: Andrea Femerstrand
set10-006.flavorText: He's determined to protect his friends, no matter what forms they take.

set10-007.author: Pix Smith
set10-007.flavorText: If you want to come with me, you may.

set10-008.author: Adam Fenton
set10-008.flavorText: Curse me kilts, have I missed trouble!

set10-009.author: Lauren Levering / Patri Balanovsky
set10-009.flavorText: If I’m correct, and I know I am, these are the plants from chapter 6 of Hana’s Herborium.

set10-010.author: McKay Anderson
set10-010.flavorText: In its reflection he could see the future: Moments from now, they'd be less hungry.

set10-011.author: Rosa la Barbera / Livio Cacciatore
set10-011.flavorText: Initiator of the STOP protocol: Strategic Termination of Progression.

set10-012.author: Brian Weisz
set10-012.flavorText: He had seen many strange things in the Mysterious Ruins, but the glowing river was the most concerning. It looked and moved like water but somehow felt... different.

set10-013.author: Casey Robin
set10-013.flavorText: Her song winds through the forest, the gentle melody soothing the hearts of all who hear it.

set10-016.author: Laura De Pascale
set10-016.flavorText: A fine mess you've gotten yourself into this time, Sebastian. If the Sea King finds out something's wrong with Ariel before we find a way to fix it, you really <will> be in hot water!

set10-019.author: Casey Robin
set10-019.flavorText: This place is just a different kind of jungle.

set10-022.author: Jiahui Eva Gao
set10-022.flavorText: I promise I'm coming home, somehow. Nothing can stop Della Duck!

set10-038.author: Kevin Sidharta
set10-038.flavorText: Untried courage is no match for his evil. %—Dallben

set10-039.author: Kendall Hale
set10-039.flavorText: My beloved warriors have come to life! All the dead of centuries past! Never has anyone created an army like this! —The Horned King

set10-041.author: Brian Kesinger
set10-041.flavorText: My power is still not enough. I need something more. Something... shadowy.

set10-042.author: Mara Tango
set10-042.flavorText: This is a strange kind of magic. These ‘whispers’ seem independent, but they're still incomplete.

set10-043.author: Renée Chio
set10-043.flavorText: That does it—now I’m really ticked off!

set10-044.author: Lauren Levering
set10-044.flavorText: At last, an opportunity to earn my Mysterious Ruins Exploration badge!

set10-045.author: Clio Wolfensberger
set10-045.flavorText: This world still has secrets to uncover.

set10-046.author: Giorgio Di Santo
set10-046.flavorText: I'm the scariest thing <in> this forest. That pumpkin head should be scared of <me>!

set10-048.author: Isabella Ceravolo
set10-048.flavorText: That was fun! Let's do it again!

set10-050.author: Alejandro Hernandez
set10-050.flavorText: Yes! Things are going exactly as sire planned. Soon the cauldron will be ours—I mean his.

set10-051.author: Cam Kendell / Alejandro Hernandez
set10-051.flavorText: It’s alive! Alive! I’ve always wanted to say that. —Xanatos

set10-052.author: Matteo Marzocco
set10-052.flavorText: I am the stuff of nightmares lurking in the hidden recesses of your mind!

set10-056.author: Javi Salas
set10-056.flavorText: I'm kind of on a schedule here—I got plans for August.

set10-057.author: Matteo Marzocco
set10-057.flavorText: Here, hold this while l get help. Try not to go anywhere.

set10-069.flavorText: I tell ya, for a spooky forest, this place is all right. Plenty of berries, lots of trees for back-scratching... A bear could do a lot worse.

set10-070.author: Jochem van Gool
set10-070.flavorText: Thou art pretty as a brawl Thy hair's as dark as a moonless night Thy cheeks the red of leaves in fall— I love to sit and watch you fight

set10-072.author: Sergio Mancinelli
set10-072.flavorText: It's bessst to play it s-ssafe.

set10-073.author: Rosa la Barbera / Livio Cacciatore
set10-073.flavorText: It’s happening! IT’S HAPPENING! There's a whisper nearby, and I get to see it!

set10-075.author: Jochem van Gool
set10-075.flavorText: His commitment to excellent craftsmanship is unparalleled.

set10-078.author: Jochem van Gool

set10-080.flavorText: Hana's Herborium? The book that Illumineer wrote? Our only copy has been checked out, sadly.

set10-090.author: Shavrin Ivan
set10-090.flavorText: Follow me, if you can, Akela said, bounding into the Bitterwood. The hunt is on!

set10-103.flavorText: Be careful when gathering herbs in the Inkwell Caverns. You never know who's watching. —Hana's Herborium

set10-105.author: Marcel Berg
set10-105.flavorText: Wanna race? Last one through the Inkwell Caverns is a codfish!

set10-106.author: Devin Elle Kurtz
set10-106.flavorText: Okay, now we know pixie dust doesn’t affect the torn lorebook pages. Thanks, Tink. —Venturo, an Illumineer

set10-107.flavorText: Her name means protection, and she'll do anything to defend the cubs under her care.

set10-108.author: Mariana Moreno

set10-109.author: Shavrin Ivan
set10-109.flavorText: With cubs to protect, any strange sound must be investigated.

set10-110.author: Malia Ewart
set10-110.flavorText: The world is a cruel place, and sometimes you've got to be a little cruel to get by.

set10-111.flavorText: She danced the night away, hoping to find someone who could keep up with her.

set10-112.author: Rodrigo Camilo

set10-120.author: Cam Kendell
set10-120.flavorText: If they think we're beasts and monsters...

set10-122.flavorText: Now, you can let me look the place over, or I can come back with a warrant and a lot more cops. Your call.

set10-127.author: Aisha Durmagambetova
set10-127.flavorText: Hold on, schoolmaster! That’s a mighty big book. Let me take that for you!

set10-137.author: Andrew Chesworth
set10-137.flavorText: More torn lorebook pages! Who could have done this?

set10-139.author: Pauline Voss

set10-140.author: Alibeth Zermeno

set10-141.author: Alan Batson

set10-142.author: Kapik
set10-142.flavorText: Small glimmers may feel safe in the jungle around the Mysterious Ruins, where they can easily go unnoticed. —Hana’s Herborium

set10-143.author: Mariana Moreno
set10-143.flavorText: Well, <that> should slow you down for a minute.

set10-144.author: Kenneth Anderson
set10-144.flavorText: Ach, close the secret entrance! You're letting all the mysterious air out!

set10-146.author: Veronica Di Lorenzo / Livio Cacciatore

set10-147.author: Kendall Hale
set10-147.flavorText: Whoa! The wind's all of a sudden on the move here.

set10-151.author: Victor "Yano" Covarrubias

set10-152.author: Laura Galiano

set10-157.author: Liz Richards

set10-160.author: Victor "Yano" Covarrubias / Bryan Turner

set10-172.author: Carmine Cassese
set10-172.flavorText: Let's show those rotten ghosts who's in charge! You go first.

set10-175.author: SGeer

set10-177.author: SOWSOW
set10-177.flavorText: Stand back. I'll handle this. —Inspector Tezuka

set10-179.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set10-179.flavorText: It's time to make a stand!

set10-181.author: Brianna Garcia
set10-181.flavorText: It's hard to catch a ghost without going somewhere spooky.

set10-182.author: Mara Tango
set10-182.flavorText: You may have bested me before, McDuck, but not this time!

set10-186.author: Hana Augustine
set10-186.flavorText: Hooray! A whole new forest to be lost in! Yeah, lost in!

set10-188.author: Simone Giovanardi
set10-188.flavorText: It's the role of a lifetime, and it'll take every bit of his considerable charm and fabulous mane to get it right.

set10-194.author: Cristian Romero
set10-194.flavorText: If you hear hoofbeats in the dark, don’t look back.

set10-208.author: Clio Wolfensberger
set10-208.flavorText: This world still has secrets to uncover.

set10-211.author: Rosa la Barbera / Livio Cacciatore
set10-211.flavorText: It’s happening! IT’S HAPPENING! There's a whisper nearby, and I get to see it!

set10-212.author: Mariana Moreno
set10-212.flavorText: It's hard to tell where the branches end and the snake begins.

set10-214.author: Devin Elle Kurtz
set10-214.flavorText: Okay, now we know pixie dust doesn’t affect the torn lorebook pages. Thanks, Tink. —Venturo, an Illumineer

set9-002.author: Grace Tran
set9-002.flavorText: We’ll find our way. I know we will!

set9-003.author: Simangaliso Sibaya
set9-003.flavorText: The best part about a beachside concert is that there’s always room for one more.

set9-004.author: Grace Tran
set9-004.flavorText: His heart warmed as the music began and the dancers took their places.

set9-006.flavorText: The other princesses were especially happy to attend her long-awaited celebration.

set9-007.author: Eva Widermann
set9-007.flavorText: Don’t question her. Don’t doubt her. And above all, don’t disobey her.

set9-008.author: Aubrey Archer
set9-008.flavorText: We can all make the world a little brighter in our own way.

set9-009.author: Aisha Durmagambetova
set9-009.flavorText: Moving to the music, he begins to understand the true meaning of ohana and how he fits into the family he has found.

set9-010.author: Amber Kommavongsa
set9-010.flavorText: Everything looks better when you’re free to be yourself.

set9-011.author: Kendall Hale
set9-011.flavorText: She has a talent for thwarting hidden schemes.

set9-012.author: Aisha Durmagambetova
set9-012.flavorText: Plenty of berries—and friendship—to go around.

set9-013.author: Dave Beauchene
set9-013.flavorText: As long as he’s around, newcomers to the Great Illuminary will always get a warm welcome.

set9-015.author: Matthew Robert Davies
set9-015.flavorText: Watch and you’ll see—some day I’ll be part of your world!

set9-016.author: Kenneth Anderson
set9-016.flavorText: When you need help, his is the first face you want to see.

set9-021.author: Jiahui Eva Gao
set9-021.flavorText: He just can't wait for new friends to arrive!

set9-022.author: Angie Simpson
set9-022.flavorText: This magic will certainly do the trick.

set9-023.author: Brianna Garcia
set9-023.flavorText: The more of the Inklands she claims, the more she wants.

set9-024.author: Marcel Berg
set9-024.flavorText: So you’re from outer space, huh? I hear the surfing’s choice. —David

set9-035.author: Matthew Robert Davies
set9-035.flavorText: Sublime beauty matched with peerless cunning. Is there any question who is fairest?

set9-037.author: John Loren
set9-037.flavorText: The secret contract has already been written.

set9-038.author: Marcel Berg
set9-038.flavorText: There's more than one way to bury secrets.

set9-039.author: Angelina "Spikie" Ricardo
set9-039.flavorText: No matter what she tried, Belle couldn’t completely heal Beast’s wound.

set9-040.author: Malia Ewart
set9-040.flavorText: The mixed ink had changed more than just the rose.

set9-041.author: John Loren
set9-041.flavorText: He’d always felt a kinship with honey. They were both golden, and sweet, and likely to end up in sticky situations.

set9-043.author: Matthew Robert Davies
set9-043.flavorText: Ice is stronger than you may think.

set9-047.author: Grace Tran
set9-047.flavorText: Stick with me, kid, and we’ll fly all the way to the top!

set9-048.author: Cristian Romero
set9-048.flavorText: The power of ice may not stop the flood, but it will help protect Lorcana.

set9-049.author: Michaela Martin
set9-049.flavorText: So there I was. Perfectly in control of the situation.

set9-050.author: Kenneth Anderson
set9-050.flavorText: That cursed beast liked the taste of me so well he’s followed me ever since.... —Captain Hook

set9-053.author: Nicholas Kole
set9-053.flavorText: Recreated by magical ink, Elsa found herself in an entirely new world. Fortunately, ice works the same way everywhere.

set9-054.author: Koni
set9-054.flavorText: Right here, direct from the lamp, right here for your very much wish fulfillment.

set9-055.author: Giulia Riva
set9-055.flavorText: I’m Olaf and I like warm hugs!

set9-057.author: Cristian Romero
set9-057.flavorText: That’s the way to give it what it needs, Juju!

set9-058.author: Juan Diego León
set9-058.flavorText: This rock? No problem. Go get that prophecy, hermana!

set9-059.author: Veronica Di Lorenzo / Livio Cacciatore
set9-059.flavorText: I will rule as far as the eye can see.

set9-069.author: Grace Tran
set9-069.flavorText: I asked for emerald and that is clearly jade! What is wrong with you people?

set9-070.author: John Loren
set9-070.flavorText: Some days, it's nice to let the river do the running.

set9-071.author: Massimiliano Narciso / Marieke Ferrari
set9-071.flavorText: Now it's happened once or twice, someone couldn't pay the price... —Ursula

set9-072.author: Mike Parker
set9-072.flavorText: He stands ready to protect his friends from any threat.

set9-075.author: Rodrigo Camilo
set9-075.flavorText: Fast board, cool tunes—what more could you want?

set9-078.author: Stefano Spagnuolo
set9-078.flavorText: It's the Leaning Tower of Cheese-a.

set9-079.author: Aubrey Archer
set9-079.flavorText: A deal’s a deal. But falling in love was never supposed to be part of it.

set9-080.author: Juan Diego León
set9-080.flavorText: On rivers throughout the Inklands, the little steamboat's whistle answers the cheery tunes of its pilot.

set9-082.author: Mané Kandalyan / Luca Pinelli
set9-082.flavorText: I must make the hard decisions to protect my daughter, especially in this unfamiliar world.

set9-084.author: Brian Weisz
set9-084.flavorText: His name is Pegasus. And he’s all yours.... —Zeus

set9-087.author: Jochem van Gool
set9-087.flavorText: Why not stick around for dinner?

set9-089.author: Duyen Nguyen / Jared Nickerl
set9-089.flavorText: Don't be too put off by this. . . hunk of hardware.

set9-091.author: Valentina Graziuso
set9-091.flavorText: I can take <anything> apart in under five minutes!

set9-092.author: Lauren Walsh
set9-092.flavorText: Fabulously wealthy. Practically untouchable. Genuinely inauthentic.

set9-103.author: Gaku Kumatori
set9-103.flavorText: All a mob needs is a push in the wrong direction.

set9-104.author: Matthew Robert Davies / Leonardo Giammichele
set9-104.flavorText: The sixth Rule of Villainy: Keep your mind sharp and your claws sharper.

set9-105.author: Oggy Christiansson
set9-105.flavorText: He’ll join the hunt for lore after he’s had a quick snack.

set9-106.author: Sandara Tang
set9-106.flavorText: Always ready to make a splash.

set9-107.author: Javi Salas
set9-107.flavorText: Shipwrecks are great places to find lore—and hide from sharks!

set9-108.author: Luis Huerta
set9-108.flavorText: The ninth Rule of Villainy: When all else fails, turn into a dragon.

set9-109.author: Stefano Spagnuolo
set9-109.flavorText: Goin' to the Powerline concert. Ah! It's unbelievable, man. —P.J. Pete

set9-115.author: Matthew Robert Davies
set9-115.flavorText: It’s not arrogance when you really <are> the best.

set9-116.author: Mila Useche
set9-116.flavorText: No fire or storm will keep her from her goal.

set9-117.author: Kenneth Anderson
set9-117.flavorText: For the first time ever, we’re seeing it eye to eye.

set9-118.author: LadyShalirin
set9-118.flavorText: Sometimes the only way to fight the unimaginable is with the incredible.

set9-119.author: Otto Paredes
set9-119.flavorText: Come on—what's the worst that can happen?

set9-121.author: Valentin Palombo
set9-121.flavorText: The invaders are at our gates, mes amis! It’s time to show them what we’re made of.

set9-122.author: Bill Robinson
set9-122.flavorText: You’ll have to deal with them sooner or later.

set9-123.author: Valerio Buonfantino
set9-123.flavorText: The glow of lore in the flood caught her eye. The spellbook! she cried. Don’t let it get away!

set9-124.author: Clio Wolfensberger
set9-124.flavorText: Who are you? And how did you find me?

set9-127.author: Amber Kommavongsa
set9-127.flavorText: Two parts bravery, one part cleverness, and a whole lot of determination.

set9-128.author: Cory Godbey
set9-128.flavorText: Yes, sir. Righto, sir. Right away, sir!

set9-137.author: Leonardo Giammichele
set9-137.flavorText: Make sure you know what’s truly important and be willing to fight for it.

set9-138.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set9-138.flavorText: This looks like part of a larger crystal!

set9-139.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set9-139.flavorText: I got it! I knew I could do it! Dewey for the win!

set9-144.author: Luis Huerta
set9-144.flavorText: A king must care for all of the creatures in his kingdom, no matter their size.

set9-145.author: Aisha Durmagambetova
set9-145.flavorText: Isn’t it just gorgeous, darling? And just as stylish as I am.

set9-146.author: Maria Dresden
set9-146.flavorText: After talking to Olaf, Anna marched into the unexpected storm to save Kristoff.

set9-147.author: Brian Weisz
set9-147.flavorText: Excitement. . . adventure. . . danger lurking around every cor— AAAAAGGH!

set9-148.flavorText: Hans was confident he could bring Anna to Ursula—all he needed was something of Kristoff's to lure her in.

set9-149.author: Jennifer Gheduzzi / Livio Cacciatore
set9-149.flavorText: She has only one question, and she’d better like the answer.

set9-150.author: Juan Diego León
set9-150.flavorText: When he talks, even the sky listens.

set9-151.author: Matthew Robert Davies
set9-151.flavorText: He's gotta have a weakness, because everybody's got a weakness.

set9-152.author: Rogie Custodio / Erin Shin
set9-152.flavorText: You dig a little deeper, you’ll find everything you need.

set9-153.author: Nicholas Kole
set9-153.flavorText: As the princess slumbered, her power awoke.

set9-154.author: Koni
set9-154.flavorText: Her music fills the Illuminary’s gardens with joy and light.

set9-155.author: Rosa la Barbera / Leonardo Giammichele
set9-155.flavorText: She may be young, but she’s got the spirit of a true leader.

set9-156.author: Gabriel Romero / Pix Smith
set9-156.flavorText: A little ingenuity and a lot of heart will take you far in this world.

set9-157.author: Arianna Rea
set9-157.flavorText: I’ll get to the bottom of what happened with the locked lorebook. You can count on me!

set9-158.author: Jenna Gray
set9-158.flavorText: She makes every space more beautiful.

set9-159.author: Rianti Hidayat
set9-159.flavorText: When he thought, he thought in the most thoughtful way he could think.

set9-161.flavorText: They say if you dream a thing more than once, it's sure to come true!

set9-162.author: John Loren

set9-181.author: Rob Di Salvo
set9-181.flavorText: Soon you’ll learn who holds the <real> power!

set9-182.author: Gaku Kumatori
set9-182.flavorText: All he's got is his charm.

set9-183.author: Mariana Moreno
set9-183.flavorText: Not much of a roadblock, but I suppose I’ll do.

set9-185.flavorText: He sets the standard for intrepid adventurers everywhere.

set8-002.flavorText: Snakes? Firing lasers? In a secret underground lair? No problem!

set8-004.author: Carlos Luzzi

set8-008.author: Emily Abeydeera

set8-010.author: Arianna Rea

set8-011.author: Erika Wiseman

set8-012.author: Kendall Hale
set8-012.flavorText: Family is family no matter what.

set8-014.author: Carmine Pucci

set8-016.author: Jake Murphy

set8-017.author: Mariana Moreno
set8-017.flavorText: His training was invaluable in infiltrating the palace.

set8-021.author: Francesco D'ippolito / Malia Ewart

set8-025.author: Oggy Christiansson
set8-025.flavorText: Sand sure was more fun than it looked!

set8-029.author: Joy Ang / Jaime Puga
set8-029.flavorText: The only power you need is the power of AWESOMENESS! —Rhino

set8-031.author: Denny Minonne
set8-031.flavorText: He knows the way through. Just try to keep up! —Antonio

set8-034.author: Simone Buonfantino
set8-034.flavorText: I’m sorry I held on too tight.

set8-036.author: French Carlomagno
set8-036.flavorText: If you need fixin’, ol' Joey’s on the job.

set8-038.author: Gwawi
set8-038.flavorText: Oh boy! A new friend to play with!

set8-045.author: Eva Widermann
set8-045.flavorText: All of the power of the normal guards, with none of the insolence. —Jafar

set8-046.author: Alex Accorsi
set8-046.flavorText: They’ve always been here. Waiting for a moment of weakness to attack. —Sisu

set8-048.author: Marcel Berg
set8-048.flavorText: Don't forget—I'm the guy with the leverage here.

set8-051.author: Natalia Trykowska
set8-051.flavorText: I’m not in the vision business right now. I’m in the stopping you business.

set8-053.author: Rachel Elese
set8-053.flavorText: Wait'll they get a whiff of this . . .

set8-054.author: Samanta Erdini
set8-054.flavorText: The sooner we get this done, the sooner I'm free . . . of you.

quest2-055.author: Amber Kommavongsa
quest2-055.flavorText: Fear is what can't be trusted.

quest2-056.author: Lisanne Koeteeuw
quest2-056.flavorText: Sheesh, what is it with this high sultan guy? Can't he put in stairs like a normal person?

set8-056.flavorText: Sheesh, what is it with this high sultan guy? Can't he put in stairs like a normal person?

set8-057.author: Heidi Neunhoffer
set8-057.flavorText: As he grew older, he began to understand his responsibilities to all the creatures of the woods.

set8-058.author: Kamil Murzyn
set8-058.flavorText: Sister, dear, if we turn all the townspeople into frogs, who will give us our gold and turnips?

set8-059.author: Wouter Bruneel
set8-059.flavorText: They think they know my tricks... Oh, this one’s going to be marvelously malicious!

quest2-060.author: Hedvig H-S
quest2-060.flavorText: I have to protect my sister. You're not going anywhere!

set8-060.author: Hedvig H-S
set8-060.flavorText: I have to protect my sister. You're not going anywhere!

set8-065.author: Teresita Q. / SCG
set8-065.flavorText: He's identical to Brutus in temperament and toothiness.

set8-075.author: Carlos Gomes Cabral
set8-075.flavorText: My primo Camilo won’t stop until he makes you smile today. —Mirabel

set8-076.author: Sandra Rios
set8-076.flavorText: His sweet nature outmatches all the blooms in the meadow.

set8-085.author: Aurélie Lise-Anne
set8-085.flavorText: Helga: Sounds metallic. Could be an echo off one of the rocks. Wilhelmina: Do you want to do my job? Be my guest.

set8-087.author: Edu Francisco
set8-087.flavorText: One glance at the tiny tracks, and his protective instincts kicked in.

set8-089.author: Florencia Vazquez
set8-089.flavorText: This is so much fun, Chaca! I want to go higher!

set8-090.author: Kendall Hale
set8-090.flavorText: We need a lazard with a lizard! —White Rabbit

set8-091.author: Dustin Panzino
set8-091.flavorText: He really knows how to light up a room.

set8-092.author: Jared Nickerl / Patri Balanovsky
set8-092.flavorText: Don’t be alarmed. It is just a suit. This is not my real face and body.

set8-093.author: Luis Huerta
set8-093.flavorText: He certainly isn't the brains of the operation.

set8-094.author: Wouter Bruneel
set8-094.flavorText: You’re the fearless copilot who can handle any job.... Did I say fearless? I meant brainless! —Chip

set8-096.author: Mariana Moreno
set8-096.flavorText: Everyone knows that without rations, an operation'll be a failure. And this is why I outrank you, Lafayette. 'Cause I see the big picture.

set8-097.author: Brian Weisz
set8-097.flavorText: Don't worry, Dale! I've got you!

set8-099.author: Lisanne Koeteeuw
set8-099.flavorText: The scarab's power source! I knew that if I dug around I'd find it!

set8-102.author: Koni
set8-102.flavorText: One way or another, I get what I want.

set8-103.author: Joel DuQue
set8-103.flavorText: The tea is strong, even if he isn’t.

set8-105.author: Gonzalo Kenny
set8-105.flavorText: She’ll go wherever she pleases, no matter who she has to step on to get there.

set8-112.author: Raquel Villanueva
set8-112.flavorText: Settle in, ye wee pups, and let Uncle Jock tell ye a story about some Illumineers and a mad adventure...

set8-121.author: Rudy Hill / Denny Minonne
set8-121.flavorText: I’ve got tricks for my opponents <and> treats for my fans!

set8-122.author: Valentina Graziuso
set8-122.flavorText: Say, jewels just lying around in a fancy joint like this? It would be a shame if a few went missing...

set8-124.author: French Carlomagno
set8-124.flavorText: I can handle anything you throw at me... Wait, are those <laser snakes>? This is the best track ever!

set8-125.author: Teresita Q. / SCG
set8-125.flavorText: He's identical to Nero in cruelty and classiness.

set8-126.author: Filipe Laurentino
set8-126.flavorText: And there I was in the cave below the palace when suddenly sand began pouring down. Did I stop? No! What's a little sand?

set8-127.author: Filipe Laurentino
set8-127.flavorText: Goodness, those scarabs are awfully close! We must find the way out!

set8-128.author: Heidi Neunhoffer
set8-128.flavorText: Sacrebleu! This is no way to treat a guest in your palace!

set8-129.author: Samoldstoree
set8-129.flavorText: Take this magical stone. You'll need it to keep up with me!

set8-130.author: Kuya Jaypi
set8-130.flavorText: Move, move, move! There’s no time to explain. Well, maybe a little time, so listen up...

set8-131.author: Yu Nguyen
set8-131.flavorText: You were so focused on me and Mulan that you forgot about my man Cri-Kee here. And that was a <mistake>! —Mushu

set8-132.author: Sara Leal (Loyal)
set8-132.flavorText: What are we guarding the kitchen for, Napoleon? There ain't no scarabs 'round here. Call me when there's somethin' serious that needs fixin'.

set8-133.author: Saulo Nate
set8-133.flavorText: Say hello to Figaro. Up to mischief already! —Geppetto

set8-134.author: Oggy Christiansson
set8-134.flavorText: C'mon! Let's show that mean old high sultan what’s what.

set8-138.author: Simone Buonfantino
set8-138.flavorText: LeFou, sometimes you really take the cake. —Gaston

set8-143.author: noc4urne
set8-143.flavorText: You can't do this to me, you swindler! We had a verbal agreement!

set8-144.author: James Rey Sanchez
set8-144.flavorText: Sand? In the forest? I’ll bet some magical miscreant’s up to no good. Well, it’s none of my concern. I’m going back to bed.

set8-146.author: Denny Minonne
set8-146.flavorText: Even a frightened lion still has claws.

set8-153.author: Jon Densk / Hayley Evans
set8-153.flavorText: After that dreadful Ratigan business, I know about villains. This Jafar is certainly a villain of the highest order.

quest2-156.author: Matt Chapman
quest2-156.flavorText: It began with two sisters. One born with magical powers, and one born powerless. Their love of snowmen, infinite.

set8-156.author: Matt Chapman
set8-156.flavorText: It began with two sisters. One born with magical powers, and one born powerless. Their love of snowmen, infinite.

quest2-157.author: Kapik
quest2-157.flavorText: Mom, Mom! I think I’m still growing!

set8-158.author: Jules Dubost
set8-158.flavorText: Okay, so the plan is ‘leave Wasabi to watch our backs while we steal the crown.' Good to know.

set8-159.author: Jennifer Wu
set8-159.flavorText: Check it out! This ‘ink’ offers so many possibilities.

set8-160.author: Giulia Riva
set8-160.flavorText: Time to try something new, dear.

set8-161.author: Julie Vu
set8-161.flavorText: Now, don't fret over the mess, love. We'll have everything shipshape in no time.

set8-163.author: Andrea Parisi
set8-163.flavorText: As Skippy's older sister, she's had lots of experience putting things back together.

set8-164.author: Lisanne Koeteeuw
set8-164.flavorText: Beautiful music can ennoble one’s spirit, no matter how dire things seem.

set8-168.author: Edu Francisco
set8-168.flavorText: Do you want to be all muscle and no brain? —Merlin

set8-169.author: McKay Anderson
set8-169.flavorText: Miss Bianca, over here! I found something!

set8-172.author: Anderson Mahanski
set8-172.flavorText: Jafar will never expect us to hide lore from him in his own safe! How exciting!

set8-173.author: Malia Ewart
set8-173.flavorText: This little thing has a much more rudimentary design than if I had created it. But if you were rushing development, then this makes sense.

set8-174.author: Malia Ewart
set8-174.flavorText: Everything he carves is a work of art.

set8-181.author: French Carlomagno
set8-181.flavorText: Spears of Fang, stand strong and tall. We are the last line of defense and we will not fall!

set8-182.author: Adam Fenton
set8-182.flavorText: You come at me, you get the beak, capisce?

set8-185.author: Adam Fenton
set8-185.flavorText: Say, let me do it, Mad Dog. It's my turn.

set8-186.author: Ornella Savarese
set8-186.flavorText: How dare you? Arm yourself, scoundrel!

set8-187.author: Kendall Hale
set8-187.flavorText: A single grain of rice can tip the scale. One man may be the difference between victory and defeat. —The Emperor

set8-190.author: Irish Chua
set8-190.flavorText: This place is scarier than Prince John.

set8-191.author: Carmine Pucci
set8-191.flavorText: In dark times, a crown is a weighty honor we must bear with grace and courage.

set8-193.author: Defne Tözüm
set8-193.flavorText: When the whole world changes around you, remember that Khan will always be the same—steadfast and true. —Fa Zhou

set8-194.author: Cam Kendell
set8-194.flavorText: That’s quite a predicament you’re in. Glad it ain’t me.

set8-195.author: Carlos Luzzi
set8-195.flavorText: Nice try, chumps! Too bad I’m all the way up here!

set8-196.author: Edu Francisco
set8-196.flavorText: Flint's secret trove was never found, but stories have persisted that it remains hidden.. . —Narrator

quest2-197.author: Ha Jung Song
quest2-197.flavorText: Never be afraid to make a big entrance.

set8-197.author: Ha Jung Song
set8-197.flavorText: Never be afraid to make a big entrance.

quest2-200.author: Jeanne Plounevez / Andrew Theophilopoulos
quest2-200.flavorText: Ah! Finally, a good use for his destructive instincts. —Jumba Jookiba

set8-200.author: Jeanne Plounevez / Andrew Theophilopoulos
set8-200.flavorText: Ah! Finally, a good use for his destructive instincts. —Jumba Jookiba

set8-223.author: Carlos Luzzi
set8-223.flavorText: You're just in time for Surprise à la Goof!

quest2-001.author: Stefano Zanchi
quest2-001.flavorText: Don't forget, you are awesome. You can handle anything. Now channel your inner awesomeness and CLEAR THIS TRAP!

set7-001.author: Stefano Zanchi
set7-001.flavorText: Don't forget, you are awesome. You can handle anything. Now channel your inner awesomeness and CLEAR THIS TRAP!

set7-003.author: Mike Parker
set7-003.flavorText: Every parent struggles with getting their baby to sleep. Kings are no different.

set7-005.author: Hedvig H-S
set7-005.flavorText: The best part of completing the obstacle course was finding their human at the end.

quest2-006.author: César Vergara / Eri Welli
quest2-006.flavorText: Look, the code may say I’m a princess, but I know who I really am....

set7-006.author: Yu Nguyễn
set7-006.flavorText: As my grandpappy, Old Reliable, used to say, save your energy for when it matters.

set7-007.author: Mariana Moreno
set7-007.flavorText: She was born to be a star no matter where she performed.

set7-008.author: Kapik
set7-008.flavorText: The devoted mice were excited to surprise Cinderella with a new dress. Smiling, Archazia gave them a spool of magic thread. This will make it perfect, she said.

set7-013.author: Koni
set7-013.flavorText: My family's amazing, and I'm in my family, so...

set7-015.author: Tania Soler
set7-015.flavorText: But, you see, I have the other slipper.

set7-016.author: Samanta Erdini
set7-016.flavorText: The puzzles of the heart are trickier than anything Archazia could come up with.

quest2-018.author: Ellie Horie
quest2-018.flavorText: Super dog versus super log! This is AWESOME! —Rhino

set7-018.author: Ellie Horie
set7-018.flavorText: Super dog versus super log! This is AWESOME! —Rhino

set7-019.author: Aubrey Archer
set7-019.flavorText: Once Pascal got into Archazia’s flowerbeds, there was no getting him out.

set7-022.author: Stefano Spagnuolo
set7-022.flavorText: A trap is just a puzzle that's not very friendly.

set7-025.author: César Vergara
set7-025.flavorText: I just made something unexpected. Something sharp, something new.

set7-027.author: Eri Welli
set7-027.flavorText: I got that medal in the bag.

set7-029.author: Cécile Carre
set7-029.flavorText: Tricks and traps are nothing for plucky pups.

set7-033.author: Mario Manzanares
set7-033.flavorText: A true heart can thwart many an evil scheme.

set7-034.author: Jeanne Plounevez
set7-034.flavorText: And then they were like, ‘How’d you catch so many fish, Koda?’ And I said, ‘Well, you know me. I <know> how to catch fish.’ And they said...

set7-036.author: Alice Pisoni
set7-036.flavorText: Preparation and luck—you can only rely on one to win a fight!

set7-037.author: Valentina Graziuso
set7-037.flavorText: Archazia’s calming presence helped Pepa dispel her dark mood.

set7-046.author: Filipe Laurentino
set7-046.flavorText: This is a place of wonder and learning. Pay attention to the Owl and see what she can teach you.

set7-047.author: Alexandria Neonakis
set7-047.flavorText: At last, after all my years of searching! —Jafar

set7-048.author: Alexandria Neonakis
set7-048.flavorText: It's said to be a bridge between us and the magic of nature.

set7-051.author: John Loren / Nicholas Kole
set7-051.flavorText: Now that the Hexwell Crown is finally mine, no force in Lorcana can stand against me!

set7-052.author: Cristian Romero
set7-052.flavorText: ... You get a whole lotta gain.

set7-055.author: Amber Kommavongsa
set7-055.flavorText: Fear is what can't be trusted.

set7-056.author: Jocelyn Sepulveda
set7-056.flavorText: She only wants rules so she can break them! —Archimedes

set7-058.author: Max Grecke
set7-058.flavorText: You wanna get to Te Fiti, you have to go through a whole ocean of bad. Not to mention Te Kā. —Maui

set7-059.author: Oggy Christiansson
set7-059.flavorText: Yes, I’ve already finished this course. I'm still going to bounce a few more times.

set7-060.author: Kenneth Anderson
set7-060.flavorText: Oh, hang on. I love this bit! He pops the balloon and all those acorns go flying out. Gets me every time. —Kronk

set7-061.author: Arianna Rea
set7-061.flavorText: Um, wasn’t there something the boss wanted us to take care of? Was it testing these arrows?

set7-062.author: Andrea Femerstrand
set7-062.flavorText: He may be spectral, but the danger is very real.

set7-073.author: Eri Welli
set7-073.flavorText: When it comes to magic spells, proper pronunciation is key.

set7-075.author: Arianna Rea
set7-075.flavorText: What the boss doesn’t know won’t hurt us. Much. I hope.

set7-076.author: Luis Huerta
set7-076.flavorText: Archazia’s library was a treasure trove of knowledge even for such an educated owl.

set7-077.author: Jocelyn Sepulveda
set7-077.flavorText: You presume much, to think you are welcome here.

set7-078.author: Samanta Erdini
set7-078.flavorText: She heard Mariano’s heart skip a beat. Was it because of the puzzle, or was he looking at her?

set7-085.author: Rianti Hidayat
set7-085.flavorText: Once again, Drizella was confronted with a simple truth: life wasn’t fair.

set7-086.author: Simangaliso Sibaya / Mario Manzanares
set7-086.flavorText: He loves two things: explosions and even more explosions.

set7-087.author: McKay Anderson
set7-087.flavorText: Processing data from Archazia's thought scrolls is taking a great deal of power. Extreme battery saver protocol engaged.

set7-088.author: Kasia Brzezinska
set7-088.flavorText: There's nothing he can’t talk his way out of.

set7-089.author: Serena Wade
set7-089.flavorText: I wasn't stealin' it! I was just keepin' it safe.

set7-090.author: Jennifer Wu
set7-090.flavorText: Even with a mind as brilliant as his, the mixed ink was a unique puzzle to solve.

set7-091.author: Sandara Tang
set7-091.flavorText: He's not your average cat, after all. Then again, what cat is? —Archazia

set7-092.author: Stefano Zanchi
set7-092.flavorText: He'd be the first to tell you he's as magnificent as he is deadly.

set7-093.author: Valerio Buonfantino
set7-093.flavorText: The final part of the crown! Jafar will be pleased.

set7-097.author: Diogo Saito
set7-097.flavorText: In the hands of a lesser person, this much power would be irresponsible.

set7-098.author: João Moura
set7-098.flavorText: Aye aye, Captain! I’ll get it done.

set7-099.author: Geoffrey Boudout
set7-099.flavorText: Look what I found! Can we stay here and play?

set7-100.author: Sara Leal (Loyal)
set7-100.flavorText: Are you sure we’re allowed in here? Jim Dear would never allow me in the kitchen.

set7-101.author: Mel Milton
set7-101.flavorText: One of these must be the right lever, but I’ll be a llama’s aunt if I can figure out which one...

set7-102.author: Luca Pinelli
set7-102.flavorText: He liked to prepare for any emergency. They happened frequently with Kuzco around.

set7-103.author: Alice Pisoni
set7-103.flavorText: You can’t leave yet! Don’t you want to hear the ending? —Tweedledee

set7-107.author: João Moura
set7-107.flavorText: All right now, crew–we’ve a lot to do today!

set7-108.author: Emily Abeydeera
set7-108.flavorText: A captain must be inventive, commanding, and unafraid of trampolines.

set7-111.author: Isaiah Mesq
set7-111.flavorText: You there! You can’t be here in the state you’re in. Begone before the Queen sees this mess!

set7-112.author: Therese Vildefall
set7-112.flavorText: Now darlings, pay close attention to where we are. What can you learn about the Owl from the house?

set7-113.author: Rianti Hidayat
set7-113.flavorText: Out of my way! <I’m> going to be the first to finish!

set7-121.author: Javi Salas
set7-121.flavorText: Fear will get you hurt. Luck will get you through.

set7-122.author: Antoine Couttolenc / Samanta Erdini
set7-122.flavorText: Something told the Illumineers she'd had enough of the obstacles.

set7-123.author: Brian Weisz
set7-123.flavorText: Who spit in her bean curd? —Grandmother Fa

set7-124.author: Brian Weisz
set7-124.flavorText: There's no time. We have to act now!

set7-127.author: Cristian Romero
set7-127.flavorText: Cy-Bugs are like a virus. They don’t know they’re in a game. —Calhoun

set7-128.author: Saulo Nate
set7-128.flavorText: Silence is golden. And he loves gold.

set7-129.author: Kamil Murzyn
set7-129.flavorText: The Three of Hearts raised his spear and whispered to himself, While others fall, a Queen's soldier stands tall.

set7-130.author: Tony Bancroft / Lindsay Weyman
set7-130.flavorText: Top shelf? Pshaw! If it’s a book the mademoiselle wants, I’ll find a way to get it for her!

set7-131.author: Gaku Kumatori
set7-131.flavorText: Toby has the most splendid sense of smell of any hound I’ve trained. But he can be deucedly frisky. —Basil

set7-135.author: Luca Pinelli
set7-135.flavorText: Nobody knows who or what he really is or what he’s planning.

set7-136.author: Koni
set7-136.flavorText: No, no, no! This is NOT THE WAY I SEE IT IN MY HEAD!

set7-140.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set7-140.flavorText: He got what he wanted—just not the way he planned.

set7-142.author: Sergio Mancinelli
set7-142.flavorText: Now, move. That's it. Now give me a big bear growl. Scare me.

set7-143.author: Max Ulichney
set7-143.flavorText: Why stop the show when you can simply steal it?

set7-144.author: Kevin Sidharta
set7-144.flavorText: An owl in charge? Pshaw. He glared at the others. Then his eye fell on the targets set up nearby, and he brightened. But as long as I still get to joust...

set7-145.author: Stefano Zanchi
set7-145.flavorText: Okay, we rotated the globe to move the mural into position. We have the coordinates. Let's go!

set7-146.author: Leonardo Giammichele
set7-146.flavorText: All these traps, all these locks, all these machines... If they think that's going to stop me, they’ve sorely underestimated Edgar Balthazar!

set7-155.author: Samanta Erdini
set7-155.flavorText: You must move quickly before the trap resets. Go!

set7-156.author: Anna Stosik
set7-156.flavorText: Moana receives a call from the ancestors to sail to new skies and reconnect people across the entire ocean.

set7-157.author: Kamil Murzyn
set7-157.flavorText: I can help you with your problem... for the right price.

set7-158.author: Saulo Nate
set7-158.flavorText: Fascinating. This shouldn't exist, yet it does. It may be older than the Great Illuminary itself.

set7-159.author: Jochem van Gool
set7-159.flavorText: Helping her dad keep the flying debris to a minimum.

set7-161.author: Mario Oscar Gabriele
set7-161.flavorText: I say, what sort of contraption <is> this?

set7-165.author: Celeste Jamneck
set7-165.flavorText: He squeezed more paint from the tube and wiggled in delight. Archazia was fun, even if she was a giant owl. She had so many new colors to paint with!

set7-166.author: Ellie Horie
set7-166.flavorText: Find yourself another Illumineer. This one's taken.

set7-167.author: Rachel Elese
set7-167.flavorText: Pepper proves every puppy is part of the pack.

set7-168.author: Laura Pauselli
set7-168.flavorText: I want to play with the others! Can I, Dad? Please?

set7-170.author: Mariana Moreno
set7-170.flavorText: There’s been a heap of legends and tall tales about Robin Hood. All different too. —Alan-a-Dale

set7-171.author: Otto Paredes
set7-171.flavorText: Penny, dear, now don’t cry. We are here to help you. —Miss Bianca

set7-173.author: Victor "Yano" Covarrubias / Milica Celikovic
set7-173.flavorText: Oh, this is wonderful! I <knew> Archazia's thought scrolls would be worth a little extra effort!

set7-182.author: Mike Parker
set7-182.flavorText: A wise leader does not shy away from difficult decisions when the safety of the pack is at stake.

quest2-184.author: Brian Weisz
quest2-184.flavorText: Looks like we’re gonna do this the hard way.

set7-184.author: Brian Weisz
set7-184.flavorText: Looks like we’re gonna do this the hard way.

set7-185.author: Alan Batson
set7-185.flavorText: Archazia: Why is he wearing a coconut? Shanzay: It’s probably better not to ask.

set7-188.author: Mel Milton
set7-188.flavorText: Every trap you disarm, every test you pass, honors us all. Well done.

set7-189.author: Carlos Luzzi
set7-189.flavorText: Mere trinkets won’t get you any closer to Jafar.

set7-190.author: César Vergara
set7-190.flavorText: At last, both halves of the crown belong to me!

set7-191.author: Rachel Elese
set7-191.flavorText: I say, Captain, do you hear something? —Peter Pan

set7-193.author: Jochem van Gool
set7-193.flavorText: Okay this is it, time to show 'em your man walk. —Mushu

set7-195.author: Maria Dresden
set7-195.flavorText: We’ll reach the top of this tower in no time if we work together, darling.

set7-196.author: Amanda MacFarlane
set7-196.flavorText: Do you see this pillar? Even after it has fallen, it still can serve a purpose.

set7-200.author: Leonardo Giammichele
set7-200.flavorText: He leads the way with a steadfast heart.

set6-001.author: Omar Lozano
set6-001.flavorText: I say, land who! Er, ho—land ho!

quest2-002.author: Grzegorz Krysiński
quest2-002.flavorText: You can’t keep me away from the fun!

set6-002.author: Grzegorz Krysiński
set6-002.flavorText: You can’t keep me away from the fun!

set6-004.author: Wouter Bruneel
set6-004.flavorText: I keep fixin’ this same ding-danged hole! I should start charging overtime, plus 10 percent.

set6-005.author: Marco Giorgianni
set6-005.flavorText: Look at that water, and those birds! Wow. Wait 'til Timon and Pumbaa see this!

set6-006.author: Ron Baird
set6-006.flavorText: Come on, Dale—this is no time for hanging around!

set6-007.author: Ron Baird
set6-007.flavorText: But Chip, hanging around is what I do best!

set6-008.author: Valentin Palombo
set6-008.flavorText: Grab a board and come on out! Choice waves today.

set6-010.author: Luca Pinelli
set6-010.flavorText: Dance little friends—fill the air with light and joy. Achidanza! It is like seeing music come to life.

quest2-013.author: Simone Buonfantino
quest2-013.flavorText: There’s only one thing I like more than cheese—nothin’.

set6-013.author: Simone Buonfantino
set6-013.flavorText: There’s only one thing I like more than cheese—nothin’.

set6-016.author: Marine Josephine
set6-016.flavorText: The only way to get what you want in this world is through hard work.

set6-017.author: Aisha Durmagambetova
set6-017.flavorText: I want an expert on this planet in here now!

set6-021.author: Gianluca Barone
set6-021.flavorText: My, you’ve had an awfully big adventure. Now it’s time to rest.

set6-022.author: Samoldstoree
set6-022.flavorText: See? I <told> you it was dangerous out there!

set6-023.author: Gianluca Barone
set6-023.flavorText: Look at all my ships, mama! We’re going on the Azurite Sea!

set6-024.author: Amanda Duarte / Julio Cesar
set6-024.flavorText: Come on in. Good to see you.

set6-026.author: César Vergara
set6-026.flavorText: Always ready in an emergency—usually because he caused it.

set6-036.author: Denny Minonne
set6-036.flavorText: You could say I’m big on the <catch>, not so much on the <release>.

set6-038.author: Stefano Zanchi
set6-038.flavorText: For the indecisive sailor we have three, count 'em, <three> ships in one! It sails, it flies, it juliennes fries! All for the low price of just one wish.

quest2-039.author: Grace Tran
quest2-039.flavorText: I'm a water dragon. This is water. It's sort of my thing.

set6-039.author: Grace Tran
set6-039.flavorText: I'm a water dragon. This is water. It's sort of my thing.

set6-040.author: Cory Godbey
set6-040.flavorText: You can learn a lot of things from the flowers... —Alice

set6-041.author: Jeanne Plounevez
set6-041.flavorText: Juju! You get yourself out of that there magic, you bad boy! —Mama Odie

set6-042.author: Giulia Riva
set6-042.flavorText: The signs, they never lie. The snake thinks he’s planned for everything... Oh, ho, ho! He forgot about the owl. There’s hope yet!

set6-043.author: Malia Ewart
set6-043.flavorText: She zips through the waves without a drop of water touching her.

set6-044.author: Andrea Parisi
set6-044.flavorText: The Carpenter’s stomach growled as he clenched his hammer tight . . .

set6-045.author: Cam Kendell
set6-045.flavorText: You think you can get rid of me <that> easy?!

set6-046.author: Carlos Luzzi
set6-046.flavorText: ... While the Walrus finished off the lot, down to the final bite.

set6-049.author: Jennifer Wu
set6-049.flavorText: Go, and do not fail me. —Maleficent

set6-050.author: James Rey Sanchez
set6-050.flavorText: Clear the table? Don't mind if I do!

set6-051.author: Ron Baird
set6-051.flavorText: Carpet’s always come through for us before! He won’t let us down now. —Jasmine

set6-055.author: Alice Pisoni
set6-055.flavorText: I’ll give you a sporting chance. I’m mad about games, you know.

set6-056.author: Jared Mathews
set6-056.flavorText: One of these has got to work. Let’s see what happens.

set6-058.author: Simone Buonfantino
set6-058.flavorText: You’re not getting away from me this time!

set6-075.author: Cam Kendell / Danielle Powers
set6-075.flavorText: ... but by night... I am also a school mascot.

set6-076.author: Taraneh
set6-076.flavorText: Every Lost Boy has a favorite hiding spot. Tootles has twelve.

set6-077.author: Brittney Hackett
set6-077.flavorText: By Jove, he must be around here somewhere. Basil! Basil! Shout if—aaahhh!

set6-078.author: Veronica Di Lorenzo / Livio Cacciatore
set6-078.flavorText: Loyal butler, training target, helicopter pilot—and completely unflappable.

set6-079.author: Alice Pisoni
set6-079.flavorText: Hmm. Footprints from a large... owl? With droplets of water? Clearly some avian menace has crossed the Azurite Sea and absconded with the crown!

set6-080.author: Jochem van Gool
set6-080.flavorText: A promotion! It's about time someone recognized my natural leadership skills!

set6-081.author: Jochem van Gool
set6-081.flavorText: The answers we’re looking for are on the other side of that maze, I just know it!

set6-082.author: Gonzalo Kenny
set6-082.flavorText: Get out of my way before I run you over.

set6-083.author: Gaku Kumatori
set6-083.flavorText: A clear head and a calm hand will see you through uncharted waters.

set6-087.author: Diogo Saito
set6-087.flavorText: Sleek yet strong... These inkrunners are an extraordinary feat of engineering.

set6-092.author: Brittney Hackett
set6-092.flavorText: She had searched high and low in the Illuminary for any hint of Basil. Instead, she found something completely unexpected...

set6-104.author: Saulo Nate
set6-104.flavorText: Moana: Do you think they saw us? Maui: They saw us.

set6-106.author: Malia Ewart
set6-106.flavorText: Even the smallest mouse can make the biggest difference.

set6-111.author: Filipe Laurentino
set6-111.flavorText: Hoist the colors! Prepare to fight! Teddy bear at the ready!

set6-112.author: Lava Hijzelaar
set6-112.flavorText: Finding your way through the Azurite Sea takes a stout heart, plenty of courage, and more than a little luck.

set6-113.author: Kevin Sidharta
set6-113.flavorText: Just what we needed—a new place to fight bugs.

set6-114.author: OggysonArt
set6-114.flavorText: Port, Abu! Port! To the <left>! ABU! The other way! —Aladdin

set6-115.author: Kenneth Anderson
set6-115.flavorText: Golly, this looked a lot easier from the ship. But I know I can make it—the crew is counting on me!

set6-116.author: Cristian Romero
set6-116.flavorText: It'll take more than that to knock <me> out of the race!

set6-117.author: Koni
set6-117.flavorText: You wanna tell me I don’t know what I’m doing? I know I don’t!

set6-118.author: Filipe Laurentino
set6-118.flavorText: Get ready, Michael! Here they come!

set6-120.author: Alice Pisoni
set6-120.flavorText: Minnie leaned forward. Could it be true? Was this the island at last?

set6-122.author: Celeste Jamneck / Mariana Moreno
set6-122.flavorText: Pete was always looking for trouble. Now he was finally getting paid for it.

set6-125.author: Brian Kesinger
set6-125.flavorText: Panic, use your head for once!

set6-127.author: Cookie
set6-127.flavorText: It’s for the greater good. I’m sure you understand. —Scar

quest2-137.author: Otto Paredes
quest2-137.flavorText: My sweet subjects, I can without a pinch of hesitation assure you that I have never been so happy.

set6-138.author: Kendall Hale
set6-138.flavorText: All right, geniuses, let's feed those hungry brains.

set6-139.author: Andrea Femerstrand
set6-139.flavorText: Golly, a perfect wingnut! There's about a million uses for that!

set6-144.author: Heidi Neunhoffer
set6-144.flavorText: As the duly appointed representative for the Galactic Council, I volunteer for this assignment!

set6-145.author: Denny Minonne
set6-145.flavorText: A couple more tweaks and I’ve just about... got it!

set6-147.author: Mike Mu / Livio Cacciatore
set6-147.flavorText: You want to go in there? Fine. If you do, you won’t come back out.

set6-151.author: Samanta Erdini
set6-151.flavorText: All the clues pointed to an island, but I never thought I'd see it on a map. Golly, this is incredible! I mean, the island actually exists, so it’s technically credible—but still! This is amazing!

set6-152.author: Valentina Graziuso
set6-152.flavorText: Of course! It all makes perfect sense. That’s why my old star charts are useless. Every star in the sky here is different!

set6-153.author: Jeanne Plounevez
set6-153.flavorText: I'm not giving up on you. You don't understand this yet, but people need you.

set6-158.author: Jennifer Park
set6-158.flavorText: You are all brilliant scientists and inventors. Think of what we could do with this little device. How do we push the boundaries of what is possible?

set6-159.author: Stefano Spagnuolo
set6-159.flavorText: He'll find a way to make anything mouse-sized.

set6-171.author: Matthew Robert Davies
set6-171.flavorText: They’re very good at making trouble. —Maui

set6-174.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set6-174.flavorText: You’ve done me a great service.

set6-175.author: Carlos Luzzi
set6-175.flavorText: Captain Hook'd like a word with ya.

set6-177.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set6-177.flavorText: Anything for you, Mr. Smee! Except me share o' the plunder...

set6-178.author: Kevin Sidharta
set6-178.flavorText: Ma’am! I am a highly trained instrument of tactical superiority! Maybe we could find someone else for the gruntwork! Ma’am!

set6-179.author: Gaku Kumatori
set6-179.flavorText: I told you we’d find an island eventually! Excellent navigating. Yes, yes, I’m quite proud. Now, a toast to our success!

set6-180.author: Stefano Zanchi
set6-180.flavorText: That maze wasn’t so bad! Let’s see what this island has in store for us.

set6-181.author: Leonardo Giammichele
set6-181.flavorText: At the end of the day, it's the simplest tools that come through for you in a pinch.

set6-182.author: Michela Cacciatore / Giulia Priori
set6-182.flavorText: We’re holding steady, Captain. Despite this wind. And these waves.

set6-184.author: Mariana Moreno
set6-184.flavorText: Raya: Nothing gets past Tuk Tuk. <Nothing>. Sisu: Except butterflies! Oh, and birds! Raya: Fine. <Most> things don’t get past Tuk Tuk.

set6-185.author: Diogo Saito
set6-185.flavorText: He’ll be comin’ soon. Can’t let them find this.

set6-187.author: Hedvig Häggman-Sund
set6-187.flavorText: Gee, Donald was right—it’s spooky out here in the dark!

set6-189.author: Luis Huerta
set6-189.flavorText: Strength in numbers is overrated. I prefer my own strength.

set6-190.author: Justin Runfola
set6-190.flavorText: I'm very good at what I do. Probably the best I know.

set6-193.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set6-193.flavorText: The broken crown’s power is formidable, but not enough. With <both> halves of the Hexwell Crown, I could rule all of Lorcana!

set5-001.author: Therese Vildefall
set5-001.flavorText: I mean, I don’t want to brag or nothing, but I got some moves.

set5-002.author: Shannon Hallstein
set5-002.flavorText: The Lorcana Hide-and-Seek Championship was hers for the taking.

set5-004.author: Ron Baird
set5-004.flavorText: Let's find some nice twigs, eh? I could use a snack!

set5-005.author: Chunxi Mu
set5-005.flavorText: You have to look after your little brother, no matter how big a pain he is. —Kenai

set5-006.author: César Vergara / Eri Welli
set5-006.flavorText: Look, the code may say I’m a princess, but I know who I really am....

set5-007.author: Ron Baird
set5-007.flavorText: I'd love a snack, but I'm kinda tied up right now.

set5-008.author: Olivier Désirée
set5-008.flavorText: Peanut butter and pineapple! This’ll be the best cake ever!

set5-009.author: Hedvig Häggman-Sund
set5-009.flavorText: I’ll take whatever you’ve got . . . as long as it’s got sugar in it.

set5-010.author: Hedvig Häggman-Sund
set5-010.flavorText: Golly, this place is going to take some real fixing!

set5-011.author: Lauren Barger
set5-011.flavorText: Good evening, Lorcana! We’re here tonight to celebrate what’s possible when we stand together as one.

set5-014.author: Emily Abeydeera
set5-014.flavorText: There’s nothing we can’t accomplish together!

set5-017.author: Cristian Romero
set5-017.flavorText: I don’t think I’ve ever seen anything as sweet as this.

set5-018.author: Isabella Ceravolo
set5-018.flavorText: Investigate every part of the Illuminary, find the chromicons, restore the Illuminary, how hard can it—wait, what was that noise?

set5-020.author: John Loren
set5-020.flavorText: Thank you! Now here's a little ditty for our floodborn friends that we call 'Martin and the Flood.'

set5-021.author: Hyuna Lee
set5-021.flavorText: If he must give a victory speech, he’ll keep it brief.

set5-022.author: Jenna Gray
set5-022.flavorText: And who might you be, my knight and champion?

set5-024.author: Gonzalo Kenny
set5-024.flavorText: Oh my! Is that part of the Illuminary? I have to go help!

set5-037.author: Alice Pisoni
set5-037.flavorText: Step to it! Time is of the essence.

set5-038.author: Andrea Femerstrand
set5-038.flavorText: Don’t rush me, now—this is important.

set5-039.author: Kendall Hale
set5-039.flavorText: Hmph. What does an owl have to do to get a little peace and quiet around here?

set5-041.author: Alice Pisoni
set5-041.flavorText: Who woke up the big guy?

set5-043.author: James C Mulligan
set5-043.flavorText: Oh me, oh my! Did a piece just fall off the Illuminary?! I’ve got to tell someone before it’s too late, late, late!

set5-045.author: Samanta Erdini
set5-045.flavorText: This is just a warm-up, folks! Wait ’til you see the big finale!

set5-049.author: Brian Kesinger
set5-049.flavorText: Keep your eyes on me, folks! It's time for a little prestidigitation!

set5-052.author: Ivan Shavrin
set5-052.flavorText: The great beast breached the surface of the Azurite Sea, and the cry went out, Monstro! Monstro!

set5-054.author: Aris Zentelis
set5-054.flavorText: Evidently my invitation was lost. How dreadful. Here, let me help with the decorations...

set5-056.author: Leonardo Giammichele
set5-056.flavorText: Okay, I can totally move small stuff. I need something bigger... Where's Kristoff's sled?

set5-057.author: Brittney Hackett
set5-057.flavorText: By order of the king. You heard what she said!

set5-071.author: John Loren
set5-071.flavorText: You’re in for a real treat, Rob. Tonight's house special is my famous outlaw grub. Made from the finest whatever we could find!

set5-072.author: Kuya Jaypi
set5-072.flavorText: Oh, I guess one quick spin through the lights won't hurt.

set5-074.author: Otto Paredes
set5-074.flavorText: A-heh, heh, heh, heh, heh, hee, hee, heeeee.

set5-075.author: Eri Welli
set5-075.flavorText: Don't fuss, dear! A flick of the wrist will turn these briars into something beautiful.

set5-076.author: Eri Welli
set5-076.flavorText: The most beautiful color is blue!

set5-077.author: Oggy Christiansson
set5-077.flavorText: For a second there, I thought this might be a real challenge.

set5-078.author: Eri Welli
set5-078.flavorText: The secret to a good cake is combining everything just right. Every ingredient is important, but the magic is in how they work together.

set5-080.author: Otto Paredes
set5-080.flavorText: He won’t turn down a quick bite before dinner.

set5-081.author: Stefano Spagnuolo
set5-081.flavorText: As far as he's concerned, there's no such thing as bad taste.

set5-087.author: Alexandria Neonakis
set5-087.flavorText: What do we got here, a little snack pack?

set5-089.author: Carlos Gomes Cabral
set5-089.flavorText: A beautiful lady never stands meekly at the back of the line.

set5-090.author: Lissette Carrera
set5-090.flavorText: Golly! Those dancers can really moo-ve!

set5-103.author: Koni
set5-103.flavorText: There’s not a glimmer that can keep up with me. You might as well quit now.

set5-105.author: Federico Maria Cugliari
set5-105.flavorText: It's easy to get carried away when it comes to tug-of-war.

set5-108.author: Ellie Horie
set5-108.flavorText: Ingredients: Butter, sugar, unsweetened chocolate, vanilla, and arrogance.

set5-109.author: Dinulescu Alexandru
set5-109.flavorText: The second Rule of Villainy: Never settle for second place.

set5-110.author: Simangaliso Sibaya
set5-110.flavorText: When it comes to racing, she never gets cold feet.

set5-112.author: Raquel Villanueva
set5-112.flavorText: He loves to share the spotlight with a star like Minnie.

set5-113.author: Adam Fenton
set5-113.flavorText: The world’s most diabolical genius should never suffer such indignities!

set5-114.author: Carlos Luzzi
set5-114.flavorText: Never lose sight of where you’re going. Second place.

set5-115.author: Mike Parker
set5-115.flavorText: You'll pay for what you've done! I'll track you all the way to the Azurite Sea if I have to!

set5-120.author: Gaku Kumatori
set5-120.flavorText: His half-baked scheme to whisk away the food almost worked. But in the end, he got his just desserts.

set5-121.author: Brian Weisz
set5-121.flavorText: Hold it, boy. Not so fast. —Merlin

set5-122.author: Francesco D'ippolito / Giuseppe di Maio
set5-122.flavorText: He keeps his eye on the prize.

set5-126.author: Raquel Villanueva
set5-126.flavorText: She doesn't seek the spotlight—the spotlight seeks her.

set5-137.author: Otto Paredes
set5-137.flavorText: My sweet subjects, I can without a pinch of hesitation assure you that I have never been so happy.

set5-138.author: Rianti Hidayat
set5-138.flavorText: Look, look! My tooth is even looser today!

set5-139.author: Carmine Pucci
set5-139.flavorText: She'd seen what the ink could do for other glimmers. What could it do for her?

set5-140.author: Cam Kendell
set5-140.flavorText: The secret room should be right here! Ach, I cannot believe I paid a whole penny for this map.

set5-141.author: Carlos Gomes Cabral
set5-141.flavorText: Of <course> I'm on the list. Check under 'PJ.'

set5-142.author: Alice Pisoni
set5-142.flavorText: A little rest and relaxation will do wonders for your health, boy.

set5-147.author: Koni
set5-147.flavorText: A villainous schemer from day to night.

quest2-151.author: Matt Chapman
quest2-151.flavorText: So you see, there’s a dark void at the edge of Lorcana. A complete absence of electromagnetic radiation! What’s it made of? I don’t know! The light’s just gone. Kaput!

set5-151.author: Matt Chapman
set5-151.flavorText: So you see, there’s a dark void at the edge of Lorcana. A complete absence of electromagnetic radiation! What’s it made of? I don’t know! The light’s just gone. Kaput!

set5-152.author: Lauren Levering
set5-152.flavorText: This puts the Frosting Flinger 2000 to shame.

set5-153.author: Eva Widermann
set5-153.flavorText: This case is as good as solved! —Basil

set5-155.author: Luigi Aimé
set5-155.flavorText: There's just gotta be one of those chromi-thingies around here somewhere!

set5-157.author: Kapik
set5-157.flavorText: Mom, Mom! I think I’m still growing!

set5-171.author: Karen Hallion
set5-171.flavorText: He’s not the biggest glimmer on the team, but he still packs a wallop.

set5-172.author: Cam Kendell
set5-172.flavorText: No one will keep me from the broken crown!

quest2-173.author: Alexandria Neonakis
quest2-173.flavorText: This is my kingdom. If I don’t fight for it, who will?

set5-173.author: Alexandria Neonakis
set5-173.flavorText: This is my kingdom. If I don’t fight for it, who will?

set5-174.author: Jon Densk / Hayley Evans
set5-174.flavorText: The Illuminary can’t handle this much groove! We have to keep the noise down or it’ll fall apart for sure!

set5-175.author: Valerio Buonfantino
set5-175.flavorText: Hey, I've been turned into a cow. Can I go home?

set5-176.author: Mariana Moreno
set5-176.flavorText: Underestimating him is a recipe for disaster.

set5-178.author: Alex Accorsi
set5-178.flavorText: Maybe <this> one's a chromicon. Probably not. I really should have paid more attention when that wizard guy was talking...

set5-183.author: Aubrey Archer
set5-183.flavorText: Friendship is the best armor of all.

set5-184.author: Carlos Gomes Cabral
set5-184.flavorText: What do you mean, 'not on the list'?! I told you to <always> put me on the list!

set5-188.author: Brian Weisz
set5-188.flavorText: Well, by Jove. Don’t just stand there. Raise a glass to my son Kay . . . and may we be rid of the trickster wizard Marvin, or whatever his blasted name was.

set5-190.author: Kasia Brzezinska
set5-190.flavorText: That boy's got real spark. Lots of spirit. Throws himself heart and soul into everything he does. —Merlin

set5-195.author: Luis Huerta
set5-195.flavorText: It ain’t cheatin’ if you’re the one makin' the rules.

set4-001.author: Eri Welli
set4-001.flavorText: Falling for Julieta was the easiest thing he’d ever done.

set4-002.author: Maxine Vee
set4-002.flavorText: Let's be clear, Abuela runs this show. —Mirabel

set4-003.author: Matthew Robert Davies
set4-003.flavorText: Watch and you’ll see—some day I’ll be part of your world!

gateway1-005.author: Heidi Neunhoffer
gateway1-005.flavorText: If it’s a fight they want, we’ll be ready for them.

set4-005.author: Heidi Neunhoffer
set4-005.flavorText: If it’s a fight they want, we’ll be ready for them.

gateway1-006.author: Stefano Zanchi
gateway1-006.flavorText: Sweet Daisy, the fairest duck I ever met Each flaxen lock a rush of flowing gold Her bill the color of summer sunset Exquisite plumes, a wonder to behold

set4-006.author: Stefano Zanchi
set4-006.flavorText: Sweet Daisy, the fairest duck I ever met Each flaxen lock a rush of flowing gold Her bill the color of summer sunset Exquisite plumes, a wonder to behold

set4-007.author: Kendall Hale
set4-007.flavorText: She has a talent for thwarting hidden schemes.

set4-009.author: Hedvig Häggman-Sund
set4-009.flavorText: Who needs a gift when you’re having this much fun?

set4-010.author: Brian Kesinger
set4-010.flavorText: Yes, yes, everything will be ready. Just make sure you do your part.

set4-011.author: Andrea Parisi
set4-011.flavorText: You’ll miss her when she’s gone.

set4-019.author: Samanta Erdini
set4-019.flavorText: Why would Bruno break this prophecy? Could it be something dangerous? We have to find out!

gateway1-020.author: Kenneth Anderson
gateway1-020.flavorText: When you need help, his is the first face you want to see.

set4-020.author: Kenneth Anderson
